//-
//- FORM ELEMENTS
//- =============
//-
//- The basic structure is similar for all input types:
//- * Each form element is wrapped in a form row.
//- * The label element contains a `<span>` for label text, an `<input>`,
//-   optional inline error message and required field indicator.
//- * Beneath the label is an area for optional supplemental description text.
//-   It may contain `<p>`, `<ul>` or `<ol>` elements.
//-
//- All forms should make use of this html structure, regardless of size.
//- If used in a place where the label doesn't need to appear (such as a simple
//- search form), still include it for accessibility but hide it or move it off-screen.
//-
//- Modifier Classes
//- ––––––––––––––––
//- Add a class of `.from-row-full-width` to a `.form-row` to drop the input
//- below the label text and allow it to stretch to fill all available space.
//-
//- Contents
//- ––––––––
//- 1. Validation Error Summary
//- 2. Text Input
//- 3. Textarea
//- 4. Select Dropdown
//- 5. Single Checkbox
//- 6. Grouped Checkboxes
//- 7. Grouped Radio Buttons
//- 8. Datepicker
//- 9. Hidden Inputs
//- 10. Form Actions
//-


//-
//- 1. VALIDATION ERROR SUMMARY
//- ===========================
//- All forms should display some variation of the error summary box at the top of the form when errors occur.
//- If inline error messages are being used, this summary may only consist of a basic message.
//- If this is the only error text in the form, list each error message in a `<ul>`
//-

.form-copy.form-error
  strong Oops! Something isn't right.
  p Please check the form and try again.
  ul
    li The 'Text Input' field is required. Please supply a value.
    li Please ensure your email address is written in the correct format.
    li Please select a date.


//-
//- 2. TEXT INPUT
//- =============
//- These are the most basic form fields. Be sure to choose an appropriate type attribute
//- for this element to ensure a useful keyboard layout is shown on compatible devices.
//- Current choices are text, url, email, search and tel.
//- This input is also used for password fields.
//-
//- This example also shows how to add a required field indicator to the label text.
//-

.form-row
  label
    span.form-label-text Text Input
      abbr(title='This field is required') *
    input.form-field(type='text', name='name', placeholder='Placeholder Text')
    span.form-row-description.form-row-error-text This field is required
  .form-row-description.form-copy
    p A description of what is required.


//-
//- 3. TEXTAREA
//- ===========
//- A 'rows' attribute should be added to a <textarea> element to allow for
//- different expected quantities of text input.
//- Always try to add a textarea which visually suggests an appropriate amount
//- of text allowance for the field.
//-
//- Modifier Classes
//- ––––––––––––––––
//- If it is not possible to use the 'rows' attribute, for example if the HTML
//- is being generated by a CMS, then add a predefined class to the textarea to
//- add a height.
//-
//- Height modifier classes:
//- * .xx-short
//- * .x-short
//- * .short
//- * .normal (a textarea without a class should default to this height)
//- * .tall
//- * .x-tall
//- * .xx-tall
//-

.form-row
  label
    span.form-label-text Textarea
    textarea.form-field(name='name', rows='4') Default text
    span.form-row-description.form-row-error-text This field is required
  .form-row-description.form-copy
    p A more detailed description of what is required
    ul
      li Detailed instruction 1
      li Detailed instruction 2


//-
//- 4. SELECT DROPDOWN
//- ==================
//- If an `<option>` element's value attribute matches its text, the value
//- attribute can be omitted.
//-

.form-row
  label
    span.form-label-text Default Select
    select.form-field(name='name')
      option(value=') Choose An Option
      option(value='1') Option 1
      option(value='2') Option 2
      option(value='3') Option 3
      option(value='4') Option 4
      option(value='5') Option 5
      option(value='6') Option 6
      option(value='7') Option 7
      option(value='8') Option 8
      option(value='9') Option 9
      option(value='10') Option 10
    span.form-row-description.form-row-error-text This field is required


//-
//- 5. SINGLE CHECKBOX
//- ==================
//-

.form-row.form-row-checkbox
  label
    span.form-label-text Single Checkbox
    input.form-field(type='checkbox', name='name')
    span.form-row-description.form-row-error-text This field is required


//-
//- 6. GROUPED CHECKBOXES
//- =====================
//- To create a group of checkboxes, we use a `<span>` for the question, with
//- each answer listed in an `<li>`.
//-

.form-row.form-row-field-group
  span.form-label-text Grouped Checkboxes
  ul.form-field
    li
      label
        input(type='checkbox', name='name', checked='checked')
        span Option 1
    li
      label
        input(type='checkbox', name='name')
        span Option 2
    li
      label
        input(type='checkbox', name='name')
        span Option 3
    li
      label
        input(type='checkbox', name='name')
        span Option 4
  span.form-row-description.form-row-error-text This field is required


//-
//- 7. GROUPED RADIO BUTTONS
//- ========================
//- To create a group of radio buttons, we use a `<span>` for the question, with
//- each answer listed in an `<li>`.
//- Radio buttons from the same question must share the same 'name' attribute.
//-

.form-row.form-row-field-group
  span.form-label-text Radio Buttons
  ul.form-field
    li
      label
        input(type='radio', name='name', checked='checked')
        span Option 1
    li
      label
        input(type='radio', name='name')
        span Option 2
    li
      label
        input(type='radio', name='name')
        span Option 3
    li
      label
        input(type='radio', name='name')
        span Option 4
  span.form-row-description.form-row-error-text This field is required


//-
//- 8. DATEPICKER
//- =============
//- When necessary, we use the jQuery UI datepicker element. This is a standard
//- text field, with the addition of a wrapping `span.datepicker` element.
//- This can be used to supply a pseudo element calendar icon over the input itself.
//-

.form-row
  label
    span.form-label-text Date Input
    span.datepicker
      input.form-field(type='text', name='name')
    span.form-row-description.form-row-error-text This field is required


//-
//- 9. HIDDEN INPUTS
//- ================
//- Hidden form inputs do not need to be wrapped in any containing HTML as they
//- are not visible on page and do not need to be styled.
//-

input(type='hidden', name='name', value=')


//-
//- 10. FORM ACTIONS
//- ================
//- At the end of each form should be a form actions row.
//- This will contain any submit or reset buttons for the form.
//-

.form-row.form-row-actions
  input.button.button-primary(type='submit', value='Submit')
  input.button(type='reset', value='Clear')